[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ireland well beaten by Belgium

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Ireland have been beaten 5-1 by Belgium in the first of two internationals.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The hosts led 2-0 through goals scored by Louise Versavel and Lisa Scheerlinck but Nicola Evans pulled a goal back for the Irish before half-time.
Scheerlinck  netted her second from a penalty corner with Anouk Raes and Jill Boon adding further scores for the Belgians  in Auderghem.
Robyn Chambers and Ruth Maguire, both from Belfast club Pegasus, won their first Ireland caps in the game.
The sides meet again on Tuesday night at Waterloo Ducks club in Brussels.
Ireland are using the two matches as preparation for January's World League 2 in Kuala Lumpur.
